               <head>Gul-i ri'na of Shafiq, v. 2</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Gul-i raʿnā by Lachhmī Narāyan Awrang'ābādī "Shafīq"</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010106697 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010105563" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_3693-item1">
                     <note>
                        <p>Taz̲kirah of biographical notices for poets with quotations of their work, arranged in alphabetical order, begun 1181 and completed 1182</p>
                        <p>Consists of entries ṣād-yāʾ</p>
                        <p>Dated note on title page: June 20, 1905</p>
                        <p>Binding damaged and decaying, exposing printed Bengali texts making up fabric of boards</p>
                        <p>Dated colophon (f. 346): written by Sayyid Munavvar Ḥusayn, scribe or muḥarrir to the ministerial bar (kachirī-'i vazārat) of His Majesty, the <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="person_305855167" ref="http://lccn.loc.gov/n83055474" role="oth">King of Avadh</persName> (Oudh), at Matyā Burj, Calcutta, dated 19 Jum. I 1294/2 June 1877
                        </p>
                        <p>See IO Islamic 3692 for earlier portion of text</p>
                     </note>
